    "description": "<p>The Division of Information Technology at Horry-Georgetown Technical College is currently recruiting for a Banner Developer who will help drive a best in class user experience for our students, faculty, and staff. The developer will design and build enhancements to existing Institution ERP system (Ellucian Banner 9).</p>\n<p>Minimum Requirements: A high school diploma and six (6) years work experience in the modification and maintenance of system programs, the design and development of system, software, or the testing and debugging of system software. A bachelor's degree in a related field may be substituted for the required work experience.</p>\n<p>Preferred Qualifications: 5+ years of application administration in an institutional setting. Strong Coding Experience in at least one of the following: PL/SQL, SQL querying, JavaScript, Groovy/Grails. Experience with Evisions Argos report development tool, web development: HTML5/CSS/JavaScript/JSON, RESTful Web Services. Proficiency with Ellucian Banner 9, Degree Works, Ethos Platform and BEP. Self-directed with the ability to manage multiple projects and provide excellent problem-solving skills. Excellent written and verbal communication skills and a strong customer service approach. Experience with Ellucian Banner or similar ERP and automating and scheduling batch processes. Experience with working in a 2-year or 4-year institution.</p>\n",
