    "title": "Mobile Developer – Android",
    "description": "<ul>\n<li><em>Join the biggest native mobile team in Australia</em></li>\n<li><em>Work with passionate and creative Android developers</em></li>\n<li><em>Focus on building and progressing awesome mobile applications impacting millions of customer’s everyday</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Our Digital team is forecasted to hire a number of talented Mobile Developers for 2021. We have a wide range of positions available for both Senior &amp; Lead Android professionals.</p>\n<p>Our goal is simple – to be recognised as the #1 Digital development team in Australia. To achieve this, we are seeking Software Engineer/Senior Engineer/Lead and Specialist Engineers to help us drive innovation and transformation by placing a heavy emphasis on the craft of software development and the adoption of engineering principles.</p>\n<p><strong>The Team</strong></p>\n<p>The Commonwealth Bank mobile team is the largest native mobile team in Australia working on the Android platform. We are proud to build mobile apps which help millions of Australians manage and protect their financial wellbeing every day. We develop and create code which is elegant and simple, concise and clear using the latest technologies. We’re learning from each other every single day and innovation, passion and creativity is embedded in our culture.</p>\n<p><strong>The Opportunity</strong></p>\n<p>We’re looking for passionate Android Developers with strong native mobile application experience. You will collaborate with your colleagues to build and design mobile apps and features for 5+ million customers working on market leading digital products. Using the latest technologies, you’ll be defining future trends for the financial services industry and using your excellent problem solving skills to build high quality, technical solutions.</p>\n<p>You will have an appreciation of the value of Agile and of engineering practices. You’ll be passionate about design and writing clean and efficient code. This is an amazing opportunity to work with and learn from the best mobile engineers in the country who emphasise collaboration and communication, quality and excellence. We are a diverse team who have the same interests and goals as you, learning more about your craft from each other every day.</p>\n<p><em>These positions will be based at South Eveleigh in Sydney – our brand new state-of-the-art precinct which will soon be home to 10,000 of our people. We’re embedding ourselves in a location that will support our goal to be best in digital. We’ll be part of the wider technology community at this exciting location so the opportunity to learn and exchange ideas will be endless.</em></p>\n<p><strong>Your Experience:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Developing robust and secure native Android applications with Kotlin</li>\n<li>You keep up to date with the latest Android development practices</li>\n<li>Be eager to learn and enjoy new technologies</li>\n<li>Enjoy working on your own projects and be a part of the Android development community</li>\n<li>Enthusiasm for a great user experience</li>\n<li>Deep thinking, being logical, having imagination, design focus</li>\n<li>A strong appreciation of continuous delivery and automated testing and the value that these provide</li>\n<li>Ability to work in an Agile environment</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Please be aware that as part of our process in hiring for Android Engineers all candidates will be required to complete a coding assessment.</p>\n",
